rofessionals, offering pet care....\",\"address\":{\"@type\":\"PostalAddress\",\"addressLocality\":\"Cary\",\"addressRegion\":\"NC\",\"addressCountry\":\"US\"},\"image\":\"/images/parks/northcarolina/cozy-cats-hotel/cozy-cats-hotel-1.jpg\"}}]}25:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2d\"}}]\n2e:T4d7,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where is the main dog park in Cary, NC?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The Barkyard at Downtown Cary Park is a premier destination with separate high-energy and low-energy play zones. Godbold Dog Park and Jack Smith Park also offer excellent off-leash facilities.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Do I need a membership for Cary dog parks?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, Cary requires a dog park pass for its municipal dog parks. Single-day passes and annual memberships are available and can be purchased at community centers.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How many miles of greenway are in Cary?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Cary boasts over 80 miles of greenways. The Black Creek Greenway and White Oak Creek Greenway are extensive networks connecting parks, neighborhoods, and shopping areas.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are dogs allowed at Hemlock Bluffs Nature Preserve?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes, leashed dogs are welcome on the mulch trails at Hemlock Bluffs. It’s a great spot for a shaded, scenic walk, though it is more of a nature walk than a rigorous hike.\"}}]}26:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2e\"}}]\n27:[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"suppressHydrationWarning\":true,\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Dog Parks Directory\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Cary\\\"}]}\"}}]\n28:[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}]\n29:[\"$\",\"$L2f\",null,{\"items\":[{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"title\":\"City Overview\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-insights\",\"title\":\"Quick Facts\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"city-comparison\",\"title\":\"Top Comparisons\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-collections\",\"title\":\"Park Collections\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"neighborhood-clusters\",\"title\":\"Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-types-guide\",\"title\":\"Park Type Guide\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"title\":\"Map & Neighborhoods\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"planning-essentials\",\"title\":\"Planning Essentials\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"expert-tips\",\"title\":\"Expert Advice\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"park-directory\",\"title\":\"Full Directory\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"owner-cta\",\"title\":\"Owner & Franchise\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"faq-section\",\"title\":\"FAQs\",\"level\":1},{\"id\":\"related-resources\",\"title\":\"More Resources\",\"level\":1}]}]\n2a:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"city-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-button\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"className\":\"mobile-toc-trigger\",\"targetSelector\":\".table-of-contents\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-ul\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Contents\"}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"city-hero\",\"className\":\"city-hero-section \",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell city-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks Directory\"}],[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-chevron-right\"}],[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"children\":\"Cary\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"Greenway Capital\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Premier Play in Cary\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-chip-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"hero-chip\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-label\",\"children\":\"Greenway Miles\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-value\",\"children\":\"80+\"}],\"$undefined\"]}],[\"$\",\"div\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"hero-chip\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-label\",\"children\":\"Dog Parks\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"chip-value\",\"children\":\"3\"}],\"$undefined\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":\"Cary sets the standard for recreational infrastructure. With the stunning Barkyard at Downtown Cary Park and over 80 miles of connected greenways, it is a paradise for active dogs.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"city-rich-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"Cary, North Carolina, is widely recognized as one of the most dog-friendly towns in the Southeast, primarily due to its incredible infrastructure. Known as the \\\"Greenway Capital of North Carolina,\\\" Cary maintains \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.carync.gov/recreation-enjoyment/parks-greenways-environment/greenways\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"over 80 miles of paved trails\"}],null,\" that weave through neighborhoods, parks, and shopping districts. Trails like the Black Creek Greenway and White Oak Creek Greenway offer virtually endless opportunities for on-leash exercise, allowing you and your pup to explore miles of terrain without ever crossing a major road. This connectivity fosters a highly active dog-walking culture, where seeing neighbors out with their pets is a constant feature of daily life.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"className\":\"rich-description-paragraph\",\"children\":[\"In addition to its trails, Cary offers exceptional off-leash facilities. The crown jewel is The Barkyard at Downtown Cary Park, a beautifully designed urban space that integrates seamlessly with the surrounding park and social scene. For those seeking more traditional open play, Robert V. Godbold Park and Jack Smith Park providing fenced, secure environments with separate small and large dog areas. Like neighboring Apex, Cary utilizes a pass system for its dog parks to ensure safety and accountability. Whether you are looking for a rigorous hike on the greenway or a social hour at the Barkyard, Cary provides a premium, well-maintained backdrop for \",[\"$\",\"$L12\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/training-facilities\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"rich-link\",\"children\":\"every canine activity\"}],null,\".\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta primary\",\"targetId\":\"park-directory\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-list-check\"}],\"Browse directory\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L30\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta ghost\",\"targetId\":\"map-and-neighborhoods\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-geo-alt\"}],\"Open map\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/list-your-park\",\"className\":\"hero-cta text-link\",\"children\":[\"$L31\",\"Submit a park\"]}]]}],\"$L32\"]}],\"$L33\"]}]}